# Environment Variables

Environment variables for different deployment environments.

## Production (.env.production)
```
VITE_APP_TITLE=Masari Wellness and Spa
VITE_API_URL=https://api.serenityspa.com
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-dsn@sentry.io/project-id
NODE_ENV=production
```

## Development (.env.development)
```
VITE_APP_TITLE=Masari Wellness and Spa (Dev)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-dsn@sentry.io/project-id
NODE_ENV=development
```

## Local (.env.local)
Create this file locally for development:
```
VITE_APP_TITLE=Masari Wellness and Spa (Local)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

**Note:** Never commit `.env.local` or actual Sentry DSN to the repository.
